{"word":"πειρητίζω","slug":"πειρητίζω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πειρητίζω</b></el> <el>(πειρητζω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>epic form of <a href='S:πειράω'><el>πειράω</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to attempt, try, prove</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, or <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> <i>to make trial of</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> rei, <el>σθένεος καὶ ἀλκῆς</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>π. στίχας ἀνδρῶν</el> <i>to attempt</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>attack</i>, the lines, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}